The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Jan. 24: Sebi has amended regulations to allow mutual funds to invest in both gold and gold-related instruments. According to the amended regulations, a gold exchange traded fund (GETF) ? a mutual fund scheme that invests primarily in gold and gold-related instruments ? shall be subject to certain investment restrictions. Initial issue expenses in respect of any GETF scheme shall not exceed 6 per cent of the funds raised under that scheme, Sebi said today.

 New Delhi, Jan. 24: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has agreed to set up a task force to address exporters? problems. The group will comprise finance minister P. Chidambaram, commerce minister Kamal Nath and plan panel deputy chairman Montek Singh Ahluwalia.

 Boston, Jan. 23: Management consultant A.T. Kearney has bought the firm from parent Electronic Data Systems Corp. Financial terms of the deal were, however, not disclosed.

 Mumbai, Jan. 24: Goldman Sachs has appointed Brooks Entwistle as chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs (India) L.L.C. Entwistle will be based in Mumbai.

 New Delhi, Jan. 24: Delhi High Court today ordered the revival of defunct CRB Capital Markets after accepting the firm?s latest revival package, which includes clearing a liability of Rs 450 crore due to the public.




